= advtwit.rb

A twitter client for freaks.

== Description

This is a twitter client written in ruby optimized for twitter users having a LOT of friends.

== Dependencies

sudo gem install twitter pit term-ansicolor json

MeCab/Ruby and SQLite3/Ruby are also required.

=== Installation on Debian Linux (lenny)

- sqlite3 can be installed via apt-get: sudo apt-get install libsqlite3-ruby
- mecab needs to be manually configured
-- download mecab-*.tar.gz mecab-ruby-*.tar.gz mecab-ipadic-*.tar.gz
-- untar and do ./configure; make; sudo make install on each
-- add a line '/usr/local/lib' to /etc/ld.so.conf and sudo ldconfig

== Usage

edit etc/advtwit.cfg.rb using your favorite editor.

while true; do bin/advtwit.rb; sleep 100; done

=== advtwit web client draft

run bin/proxy.rb

access http://localhost:8000

